onst","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceRemove","isActive":true},{"text":"], at which point the timeout is automatically","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"destroyed and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the function will not be called again.  The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notify"},{"text":" function is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"called when the timeout is destroyed.  The first call to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"function will be at the end of the first ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"interval"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that timeout functions may be delayed, due to the processing of other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"event sources. Thus they should not be relied on for precise timing.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"After each call to the timeout function, the time of the next"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"timeout is recalculated based on the current time and the given interval","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(it does not try to ‘catch up’ time lost in delays)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"main-loop.html#memory-management-of-sources","type":"reference"},{"text":" for details","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on how to handle the return value and memory management of "},{"code":"data","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This internally creates a main loop source using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.timeout_source_new","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and attaches it to the global"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] using [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Source.attach"},{"text":"], so the callback","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be invoked in whichever thread is running that main context. You can do"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"these steps manually if you need greater control or to use a custom main","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"context.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The interval given is in terms of monotonic time, not wall clock time.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"See [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.get_monotonic_time"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]}]}],"metadata":{"title":"timeoutAddFull(priority:interval:function:data:notify:)","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib14timeoutAddFull8priority8interval8function4data6notifyS2i_Sis5Int32VSvSgXCSgAJyAJXCSgtF","symbolKind":"func","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"timeoutAddFull","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"priority","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"interval","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"function"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFunc","text":"GSourceFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":